  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to add a contact with their ENS address so that I don't need to use the cumbersome whisper contact code.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\nSoon users will be able to register ENS addresses inside Status, so we want to make ENS available everywhere in the app including adding a contact.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nNew > Start New Chat > Enter ENS address to chat with a contact\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nError message saying \"please scan a valid contact code\"\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\n- Change label text from \"Enter contact code\" to \"Enter contact code or username\"\r\n- For an ENS address do a lookup and see if there is a valid Status pubkey\r\n- Adapt error message if pubkey not found\r\n- Require user to type in full address (e.g. `Rachel` does not automatically resolve to `rachel.stateofus.eth`)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"318\" alt=\"ens_resolution\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/116099/42212849-96414e5a-7eb7-11e8-9eac-4d98ebc0e06a.png\">\r\n(eg allow for entering in usernames. illustration only :))",
